{
  "stem": "8423.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then she would take this little ball of dough and she'd crumble it over the top and work it really through the dough, you know, and knead it, and all that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, of course, we asked her what this special thing was, you know, about the dough.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And mother said, I had brought this little ball of dough with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When I got married, my mother gave it to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this way-- she got her ball of dough, my grandmother did, from her mother, my great grandmother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she said, and this way the bread we bake is always the same from generation to generation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And every Friday, as she shaped her seven loaves of bread, she would take a little piece again, oh, the size of maybe a tennis ball.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she would put it in this little tin box for next Friday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But one of my saddest memories concerning this bread is the last Friday before they took us to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Remembering the story so well, I stood by my mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I was watching to see what she was going to do, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And sure enough, she scooped up every morsel of that dough from her wooden kneading bowl, and shaped it into the last loaf of bread, the seventh loaf of bread.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, aren't you going to leave a little ball of dough for next Friday?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said, there is no next Friday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remembered how I used to ask her, you know, when I get married, will you give me a little ball of dough?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she said, of course she would.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
